    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "It seems the Cython-0.25.2  source tarball fetched from pipy has some security attributes set related to users and groups, that undermine untarring for me when running Docker (ubuntu:latest)\r\n\r\nHere is an example of tar erroring when trying to extract the files:\r\n\r\n```\r\n/bin/tar: Cython-0.25.2/.gitrev: Cannot change ownership to uid 96258, gid 5000: Invalid argument\r\n.... (many many more errors)\r\n/bin/tar: Cython-0.25.2/USAGE.txt: Cannot change ownership to uid 96258, gid 5000: Invalid argument\r\n/bin/tar: Cython-0.25.2: Cannot change ownership to uid 96258, gid 5000: Invalid argument\r\n/bin/tar: Exiting with failure status due to previous errors\r\n```",
    "closed_at": "2017-12-22T19:34:21Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "OWNER",
            "body": "1) GNU tar has an option `--no-same-owner` that would probably fix this (are you extracting the sdist as `root` user inside of the container?)\r\n2) 0.25.2 is about a year old by now\r\n3) consider using wheels instead of sdists\r\n\r\nClosing, please reopen if it also applies to the latest sdist and the above does not help.",
            "created_at": "2017-12-22T19:34:21Z",
